{"title":"Using and communicating Tax-Free Childcare","public_updated_at":"2015-09-07T08:30:31Z","details":{"body":"<div class=\"govspeak\"><p>HM Revenue and Customs commissioned Ipsos MORI, an independent research organisation, to conduct qualitative research to help them understand the views and preferences of eligible parents and a range of childcare providers regarding the delivery of Tax-Free Childcare (<abbr title=\"Tax-Free Childcare\">TFC</abbr>) and how the policy would be communicated. The aim of the research was to inform <abbr title=\"HM Revenue and Customs\">HMRC</abbr> decisions around the delivery of <abbr title=\"Tax-Free Childcare\">TFC</abbr>.</p>\n\n<p>The research focused on:</p>\n\n<ul>\n  <li>understanding what participants want to know about the scheme and how they would prefer this to be communicated</li>\n  <li>establishing participantsâ€™ preferences with regard to the registration process and understanding what would encourage them to register or engage early with <abbr title=\"Tax-Free Childcare\">TFC</abbr>\n</li>\n  <li>exploring participants views of a range of messages informing them about <abbr title=\"Tax-Free Childcare\">TFC</abbr>\n</li>\n</ul>\n\n</div>","change_history":[{"public_timestamp":"2015-09-07T09:30:31.000+01:00","note":"First published."}],"documents":["<section class=\"attachment embedded\" id=\"attachment_1182574\">\n  <div class=\"attachment-thumb\">\n      <a aria-hidden=\"true\" class=\"thumbnail\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/457689/Report_350_Using_and_communicating_Tax-Free_Childcare.pdf\"><img alt=\"\" src=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/457689/thumbnail_Report_350_Using_and_communicating_Tax-Free_Childcare.pdf.png\" /></a>\n  </div>\n  <div class=\"attachment-details\">\n    <h2 class=\"title\"><a aria-describedby=\"attachment-1182574-accessibility-help\" href=\"/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/457689/Report_350_Using_and_commu